gov.nih.nlm.nls.http
Class FormSubmission

java.lang.Object
  gov.nih.nlm.nls.http.FormSubmission

public class FormSubmission
extends java.lang.Object

Connect to http service, submit form query, and return result.

An example of use: 

  FormSubmission connection = new FormSubmission();
  connection.setField("InputText", inputText);
  System.out.println(connection.submit());

System Properties: 

   nls.service.authenticator: name of desired Authenticator implementation
Example of use: 
 java -Dnls.service.authenticator=<your authenticator class>
If nls.service.authenticator instance is of type nls.http.PropertyAuthImpl (the default) then set system properties: 
   nls.service.username: username
   nls.service.password: password
